<h1><font color="#5C8526">Milestone : Formal Statement of Problem 1</font></h1>
<ul><li><h2>All the elements of the set F are in the form of X --&gt; Y. Therefore, F = {X1 --&gt; Y1, X2 --&gt; Y2, ..., Xn --&gt; Yn}. A new functional dependency Xn+1 --&gt; Yn+1 is added to the set F which changes the set to F'. Since it is not necessary that the exact dependencies specified in F appear themselves in individual relations of the decomposition D. If is sufficient that the union of the dependencies that hold on the individual relations in D be equivalent to F, D must be calculated again to give D'.</h2></li>
</ul></body>
